kers to discuss informationtechnology as it relates to their agencies' missions.andM;Tuesday's featured speaker at 12:30 p.m.andP;  is Charles L. Grizzle, assistantadministrator of the Environmental Protection Agency in the Office ofAdministration and Resources Management.andP;  He will talk about how EPA usesinformation technology in guarding the environment.andM;Grizzle formerly served as deputy assistant secretary of Agriculture foradministration.andM;On Wednesday at 12:30 p.m., Juan Benitez, deputy undersecretary fortechnology at the Commerce Department, will detail how Commerce plans tomaintain a competitive edge in high technology and control export of keytechnologies in the post-Cold War global climate.andO;</TEXT></DOC>